{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}
'''Cecilia Trifogli''', [[Fellow of the British Academy|FBA]] (born 7 February 1961) is an Italian philosopher and academic. She has been Professor of [[Medieval Philosophy]] at the [[University of Oxford]] since 2008, and a [[Fellow (Oxbridge)|Fellow]] of [[All Souls College, Oxford|All Souls College]] since 1999. Her research focuses on philosophy in the [[Middle Ages]], including epistemology, metaphysics, and the reception of Aristotle's philosophy.
==Early life== Trifogli was born on 7 February 1961 in [[Rome]], Italy.<ref name="CV">{{cite web|url=http://www.asc.ox.ac.uk/userfiles/file/Addenda/TrifogliC-CV100709.pdf |title=personal CV |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2014-07-21}}</ref> She was educated at the [[University of Pisa]], graduating with a ''[[Laurea]]'' in Philosophy in 1986 and a ''Laurea'' in Mathematics in 1995.<ref name="bio - Faculty of Philosophy">{{cite web|title=Prof Cecilia Trifogli|url=http://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/members/philosophy_panel/cecilia_trifogli|website=Faculty of Philosophy|publisher=University of Oxford|accessdate=26 August 2014}}</ref> She then undertook [[postgraduate]] studies at the [[University of Milan]] from 1996 to 2000.<ref name="bio - All Souls College">{{cite web|title=Professor Cecilia Trifogli|url=http://www.all-souls.ox.ac.uk/people.php?personid=71|website=All Souls College|publisher=University of Oxford|accessdate=26 August 2014}}</ref>
==Academic career== In October 1999, she joined the [[University of Oxford]] as a lecturer in philosophy.<ref name=CV /><ref name="bio - All Souls College" /> In 2008, she was appointed Professor of Medieval Philosophy.<ref name="bio - University of Fribourg">{{cite web|title=Prof. Dr. Cecilia Trifogli|url=http://www.mediaevum.unifr.ch/espace/d/teilnehmer/trifogli.htm|website=Medieval Institute|publisher=University of Fribourg|accessdate=26 August 2014}}</ref>
She is (since 2008) chairman of the [[British Academy]] Medieval Texts Editorial Committee,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.britac.ac.uk/arp/mtmbmma.cfm |title=Medieval Texts and Medieval British Manuscripts - British Academy |publisher=Britac.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-07-21}}</ref> and president of the ‘Aristoteles Latinus’ Commission of the International Society for the Study of Medieval Philosophy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.all-souls.ox.ac.uk/people.php?personid=71 |title=All Souls College, Oxford |publisher=All-souls.ox.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-07-21}}</ref>
==Honours== In 2014 she was elected a [[Fellow of the British Academy]], the United Kingdom's [[national academy]] for the humanities and social sciences.<ref name="BA Fellow">{{cite web | url=http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/news/british-academy-announces-42-new-fellows/2014585.article | title=British Academy announces 42 new fellows | publisher=Times Higher Education | date=18 July 2014 | accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref>
