{{Infobox writer | name = Enrique González Rojo | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_name = Enrique González Arthur | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1928|10|5}} | birth_place = [[Mexico City]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = writer, philosopher and teacher | nationality = [[Mexico|Mexican]] | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = | children = | relatives = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | website = {{URL|http://www.enriquegonzalezrojo.com}} | portaldisp = }}
'''Enrique González Rojo''' in fact ''Enrique González Arthur'' (b. [[Mexico City]], October 5, 1928<ref>[http://libroclubecatepec.blogspot.com/2008/10/fue-homenajeado-el-poeta-enrique.html ''Fue homenajeado el poeta Enrique González Rojo por cumplir 80 años''] (Spanish).</ref>), is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] writer, [[philosopher]] and teacher.
== Biography == González Rojo was the only son of the writer [[Enrique González Rojo Sr.|Enrique González Rojo]].<ref name="Obra completa">[https://books.google.com/books?id=sAuroLj9pbEC&pg=PA18&lpg=PA18&dq=%22Enrique+Gonz%C3%A1lez+Rojo%22+%22mayo+de+1939%22&source=bl&ots=lhukis4q4X&sig=Kt2k8xzqVpSahvzwnyLsIN3qUUA&hl=de&ei=vlQqSsuLF4OnsAaf68meDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1 ''Obra completa''] (Spanish), p. 18.</ref> After the death of his father, he grew up at his grandfather [[Enrique González Martínez]], and the family decided, that the name of his father should not get lost.<ref>José Angel Leyva, José Vicente Anaya: [http://www.revista.agulha.nom.br/bh14rojo.htm ''Enrique González Rojo: Tuércele el cuello a la señora Posteridad''] (Spanish), November 27, 2001</ref> In 1959, he obtained the teacher's degree and a doctorate in philosophy. He taught at the [[Faculty of Philosophy and Literature (UNAM)|Faculty of Philosophy and Literature]] of the [[Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México]] and at [[Universidad Autónoma Metropolitana]], as well as the [[Universidad Michoacana de San Nicolás de Hidalgo]] and the [[Universidad Autónoma de Chapingo]].<ref>Information from Enrique González Rojo's website.</ref>
